Ahnu Nahki wrote:

&gt;What command do I use to run heritrix without using the shell script?
&gt;I just want to enter the command myself and bypass the shell script
&gt;all together.
&gt;  
&gt;
Checkout Heritrix#main and its command-line processing in 
Heritrix#doStart 
(http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/Heritrix.html#302).  
Calling Heritrix#main with a populated args array holding &#39;--nowui&#39; 
string and &#39;PATH_TO_ORDER&#39; as you were doing on the cmd-line should work 
(Also checkout the intialize method: 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/Heritrix.html#267.  
It looks for things in the environment.   Setting a system property of 
&#39;-Dheritrix.home=PATH_TO_HERITRIX_HOME&#39; on cmd-line for your wrapper or 
adding it to system properties before going into Heritrix#main will help 
heritrix find its conf, etc.).

